Pipeline-specific constraints for animation-to-live-action translation:

- Treat the system as a three-layer pipeline:
  1) Preprocess (fps normalization, scaling, audio split)
  2) Translate (video-to-video generation)
  3) Refine (upscale, smoothing, remux, QA)

- All processing steps must record deterministic metadata:
  - input paths
  - output paths
  - seed values
  - model/runtime config
  - timing

- For clip segmentation:
  - use explicit chunk boundaries
  - include overlap percentage in metadata
  - record stitch strategy used

- For retries and failures:
  - classify failure type (OOM, runtime, validation)
  - store retry count and parameter deltas
  - never silently continue after critical stage failures

- Prefer safety defaults:
  - no concurrent heavy video jobs
  - fail fast on missing ffmpeg/ffprobe
  - validate input file existence and extension before work starts

